metadata.name: th√©ba√Øde #10
metadata.description:
‚ÄúTh√©ba√Øde‚Äù is a french word for wild place, remote and peaceful, where to live in a calm retreat. It's also simply a desert and a synonym of solitude. It comes from Thebaid, an arid region of ancient Egypt and Thebes was the capital.

‚Äúth√©ba√Øde‚Äù is my debut on fx(hash), almost one year since my first works minted on Objkt (a series of Indian ink drawings, in January 2022). After learning the basics of creative coding recently, and a few works with this technique, I decided to create a first generative project. With "th√©ba√Øde" I chose to express the minimalist and narrative aspects of my artistic approach (though the title and concept emerged at the end). Gradually the work was resonating with philosophical matters I'm obsessed with since years: time, emptiness, human condition, erosion, desire, chance, combining them into a visual metaphor. The view of a vast area, a changing silhouette, an impenetrable monolith or an opening to elsewhere or nothing, day and night and day and night and dawn and dusk ‚Äî few elements able to compose a meditative and lasting tableau of questions and feelings.

Press ‚Äús‚Äù in live mode to save the work.
Made with p5js | 2023

metadata.name: Algorithm, be my guide #75
metadata.description:
At length, I summoned the courage to approach.

-

I was worn. Months of aimless wandering have culminated in this series; a meditation on my struggles to find a direction in my life and with my art.

At times paralyzed by too many possibilities, and at other times completely void of ideas. I was lost in the depths of my thinking, overwhelmed by indecision and doubt.

Generative works are a form of process art, yet along the way I‚Äôd forgotten to ‚Äútrust the process‚Äù. It was time to cede control and let each line of code light the way.

-

This project paints on a 2D canvas, pixel by pixel. I used a custom projection that blends isometric and perspective techniques, to create an uncanny viewpoint between the two. Objects are randomly generated, then an algorithm applies color mixing and position displacement to each pixel as it‚Äôs rendered.

By default the canvas has 2k pixels on its longest edge. You can change this in live view by pressing any number from 1-9. For example, pressing ‚Äò4‚Äô would render it with 4k pixels along the longest edge. I recommend ‚Äò4‚Äô, but this can take up to a few minutes to render.

Press ‚Äòs‚Äô to save the rendered image.

metadata.name: Glomularus #41
metadata.description:
Glomularus is an exploration in generative, artificial life forms. The project is an extension of my Protobyte series, begun in 2004.

Driven by Verlet icosahedra and responsive tendrils, Glomulari live in a spherical virtual ecosystem (V-eco) enhanced through user interaction.

Interaction:

Mouse/Trackpad:
  drag -> camera rotation
  drag + CMD/CTR -> camera pan
  scroll wheel/pinch -> camera zoom

Key Input:
  1-9: add acceleration
  -, +: reduce | increase V-eco sphere radius
  f, g: reduce | increase fog
  p: screen capture

Tip:
To decrease creature acceleration, reduce V-eco sphere radius

Note:
Please post your favorite Glomularus screen captures
TW: @iragreenberg
IG: @greenberg.ira

Built with Three.js, PByte.js, TypeScript, Node

metadata.name: All That Could Be #11
metadata.description:
This token was created for THE PASSAGE: Pitch Drop experience, an interactive minting experience where your choices determine the artist and design of your token. 

To take part, please purchase an Edition 5 Coin on fx(hash) by HERE & NOW.

The artwork and experience draw inspiration from the 'The Pitch Drop Experiment': the world's longest-running laboratory experiment. Since 1927, only nine drops of pitch have fallen, and it has never been witnessed live.

All That Could Be is about the inner life of pitch drops waiting for their inevitable fall.

After first learning of the pitch drop experiment and understanding what this odd hyper-viscous liquid was‚Ä¶ all I could think about was: How does the pitch feel about all of this? What does it dream of? How does it deal with this intense pressure to snap, drip and perform?

All That Could Be acts as a metaphysical microscope into the emotional state of the pitch. The anticipated explosion of energy and pain when it loses its battle with gravity‚Ä¶ as well as daydreams imagined to brighten its dark, slow existence with vibrant, static-y layers‚Ä¶ or fantasies of being anywhere else besides trapped in a funnel under a locked encasement for the entertainment/curiosity of others who just hope to see you snap into two.

For more info:
https://hereandnow.events/

Procure a coin to participate in the event:
https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/slug/here-and-now:-edition-5

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

Some key commands in live mode:

G : Toggle grain
A : Toggle aura
S : Save current resolution
1 : 3000x3750
2 : 4500x5625
3 : 6000x7500
4 : 7500x9375
5 : 9000x11250
6 : 10500x13125
(1-6 work best on Chrome/Edge)
(rendering takes longer as resolution increases)

metadata.name: The Face We Had #193
metadata.description:
The Face We Had is a series of generative, moving sculptures attempting to express the artists personal thoughts, experiences and inclinations related to meditative and altered states of consciousness. In a non-descriptive way, the piece aims to reflect the always changing nature of mind through patterns of movement and assemblages of form, color and organic shapes, endlessly revolving around a perceived point of origin.  

Although not intended as literal depictions, the elements interact in a way that could be interpreted as dance-like interactions between thought patterns, mental energy, feelings, fragments of memories and layers of personal identity. 



Interactive features:

space - pause/play
w - wireframe view
d - debug view (compute textures)
s - save screenshot

metadata.name: Supernova poppy #107
metadata.description:
Blooms come in different shapes. Poppy flowers are known for their prominent petals and vibrant colors. This series tries to capture just that.

The flower responds to touches, retracting while being held down and restored again when released, constantly changing its size and rotation.

A series of random chords and scales gets triggered on click. Pointer-down initiates the base chord, while pointer-up plays the correspondent scale, forming a complete sequence.
Sounds are made from a genuine electric Rhodes piano and comes in 2 different pitches.

Filled petals are as common as wireframe ones, and every 4th flower will be stained by burnt metallic lights pointed at them.

@computeremotions - 2022-10-13

metadata.name: change is life #13
metadata.description:
Change in nature comes as a smooth routine. The color change takes over the leaves until they fall off. And eventually green Will reappear.
It is not so for humans.
This collection looks up to nature and embraces change. At some point in life, an unexpected crisis may occur, yet it can bring new opportunities. Welcome the learning process. Embrace the growth. Face life and live.

metadata.name: Kleurstalen #93
metadata.description: "Kleurstalen" is a simple experiment that uses fxhash's iteration property to pick colors just once. In total there are 140 editions, representing the commonly used named colors in modern web browsers. Each edition corresponds to a single color from the set, allowing collectors to - in some way - own a color! Now, the question remains: who will get the color "hotpink"?

metadata.name: Act One #244
metadata.description:
Act One, where the mannequin says ‚Äútake me home and I will dance for you forever‚Äù.

This work is an exploration of using motion capture data to create digital paintings, and a little belated birthday ballet for #fxhashturnsone. 
20% of primary sales are donated to Three.js.
 
Keyboard Controls:
[P] Play / pause the dance. By default the dance is paused after a few seconds to render a painting.
[S] Save the current view (live mode).
[V] Capture a short webm video (live mode).

Mouse Controls (while dancing): 
[left drag] Rotate
[scroll] Zoom
[right drag] Pan
[right click] Save image

Best viewed in a desktop browser. The output may be different from the preview image if your frame rate is low, reducing the size of the browser window can help improve the frame rate.

Made using Three.js, canvas API and WebGL2.
The 3D model is based on https://sketchfab.com/3d-models/mannequin-dances-ballet-a24678a81a6f4b6d8f8ba0eb1a78e58b, using motion capture data from dancedb.eu. 
Test in Chrome v107.0.5304.107 and Safari v16.1.
